The paper deals with a machine learning task under covariate shift, which is a common problem in various subfields of computer science. The use of kernel methods and the focus on prediction performance suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with bias-aware prediction, which is a topic that is relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The use of regularization and the focus on risk minimization suggest that the paper may also belong to the Statistics (cs.ST) sub-category. Finally, the use of synthetic and natural datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
